  <section>
      <title>Installation</title>
      <section>
        <title>System requirements</title>
        <para>
          Computer with internet connection.
        </para>
      </section>
      <section>
         <title>What Repos needs to compile</title>
         <ul>
             <li>Java 1.4+</li>
             <li>Apache ant 1.6+</li>
             <li>Maven 1.0+</li>
         </ul>          
      </section>
      <section>
         <title>What Repos needs to run</title>
         <ul>
             <li>Windows / Linux / Mac OS X</li>
             <li>Apache 2+ HTTP server</li>
             <li>... with mod_dav and mod_jk2</li>
             <li>PHP 4+</li>
             <li>Subversion 1.2 *</li>
             <li>Tomcat 5+ supporting mod_jk2</li>
         </ul>
      </section>
  </section>
  <section>
      <title>User authentication</title>
      <para>
         <p>Authentication is configured a three different places:</p>
         <ul>
             <li>Apache configuration in the repository mapping</li>
             <li>Webapp authentication module (Acegi)</li>
             <li>PHP authentication scriptlet, in <code>conf/authenticationl.inc.php</code></li>
         </ul>
         <p>Only Apache actually verifies the login. Repos code only makes sure it has access to the credential, to be able to retrieve resources for the user.<p>
         <p>They all need to be configured with BASIC authentication, realm '<b>repos</b>'</p>
      </para>
  </section>
